<p>This is either a coding or documentation issue.</p>

<p>On these lines the loadModule.resolve is loaded, which by default is picked up by the ModuleResolverListers. The callback seems to indicate that the execution should stop after a listener has returned a class. In that case it should use triggerUntil.</p>

<p>However, since the trigger method in Zend\EventManager\EventManager also has a fourth callback parameter it might be that instead the documentation needs to be updated.</p>

